CALL FOR PARTICIPATION
______________________________________________________________________

ICALP 2010
37th International Colloquium on Automata, Languages and Programming

July 5-10, 2010
Bordeaux, France
http://icalp10.inria.fr/

Deadline for early registration: June 4th, 2010
Registration url: http://icalp2010.dakini.fr <http://icalp2010.dakini.fr/=
>

Supported by the European Association for Theoretical Computer Science=20
(EATCS) and organized by the INRIA research center in Bordeaux (url)=20
with the participation of LaBRI (url).

______________________________________________________________________


The 37th International Colloquium on Automata, Languages and=20
Programming, the main conference and annual meeting of the European=20
Association for Theoretical Computer Science (EATCS), will take place=20
from the 5th to the 10th of July 2010 in Bordeaux, France. The main=20
conference will be preceded by a series of five workshops.

*106 contributed papers will be presented in three tracks
* 6 invited plenary talks will be given by Pierre Fraigniaud, Jean=20
Goubault-Larrecq, Burkhard Monien, Joel Ouaknine, Roger Wattenhofer, Emo=20
Welzl.
* Three prestigious awards will be presented: the G=F6del prize, the EATC=
S=20
award and the Presburger award to young scientists.
* Three best contributed papers will be awarded as well.
The program is available here: http://icalp10.inria.fr/programme.xxx

_____________________________________________________________________

The city of Bordeaux is known worldwide for its architecture (listed on=20
the UNESCO World Heritage), quality of life and of course its wines.
All informations can be found here: http://www.bordeaux-tourisme.com=20
<http://www.bordeaux-tourisme.com/>

The conference will be held at the Cit=E9 Mondiale=20
(http://www.citemondiale.com/) at the hearth of the city, next to the riv=
er.

The social program will include an excursion in the old Bordeaux city as=20
well as the diner conference given in the remarkable Ch=E2teau Cazeneuve.

If you plan to stay arround before or after the conference, you will=20
enjoy an exceptional environment and variety of activities=20
(http://www.francekeys.com/english/regions/aquitaine.shtml).

Bordeaux is one hour from Paris by plane, two hours of Toulouse by=20
train. There are direct connections to cities like Paris, London,=20
Amsterdam and Bruxelles but also for FLOC'2010 attendees to Edinburgh=20
(http://www.bordeaux.aeroport.fr/en)
